{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2012}} '''Kill Haole Day''' is an annual event that some believe has occurred in some of [[Hawaii|Hawai{{okina}}i]]'s schools. On the last day of school before summer vacation, non-white students are said to harass and sometimes attack [[White people|white]] students.<ref>{{cite journal|location=Great Britain|author=Community Relations Commission|journal=New community|volume=7–8|page=267|issn=0047-9586|oclc=615546790|quote=My students talked of the High Schools' 'Kill Haole Day' when a day in the school year was dedicated to roughing up the whites.}}</ref>
In his 2009 book, lawyer and former Hawai{{okina}}i governor [[Ben Cayetano]] wrote that "Kill Haole Day" began as a news story headline about an incident between [[haole]] and local (not just Hawaiian) students. After that, "whenever there was a fight or an incident between haole and non-haole students, the news media, particularly the newspapers with their haole-dominated editorial boards, repeatedly reprised 'Kill Haole Day' in their news stories – as if it were a Hawaiian tradition."<ref>Cayetano, Ben. ''Ben: A Memoir, From Street Kid to Governor'' (Watermark, 2009), p. 531</ref>
In 1999, School Superintendent Paul LeMahieu said he is aware of "kill haole day" but is not aware of any recent incidents. Also, in 1999, it became an issue for [[hate crimes]] legislation.<ref name="starbulletin">{{cite web|url=http://starbulletin.com/1999/03/24/news/story7.html|title=‘Kill haole day’ linked to hate-crime bill}}</ref>
Newspaper columnist Lee Cataluna wrote in 2010, "In terms of actual, first-person, eyewitness accounts of Kill Haole Day, no one had any [incidents] that happened in the last three decades. Not one teacher, not one police officer, not one victim or perpetrator."<ref>{{cite news|author=Catalune, Lee|title=Responses refute existence of any recent 'Kill Haole Day'|work=Honolulu Advertiser|date=November 23, 2010|url=http://www.staradvertiser.com/news/20101123_responses_refute_existence_of_any_recent_kill_haole_day.html}}</ref>
